# =============================================================================
# Direct (top-level) dependencies. This is the SOURCE of truth.
# Generate the pinned lock with:   make lock
#   (uv pip compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt   OR   pip-compile)
#
# Reproducibility note: requirements.txt is the COMPILED, fully-pinned lockfile
# (incl. transitive deps + hashes where available). Always install from it, not
# from this file. See README "Reproducible installs".
#
# torch/torchvision are deliberately NOT pinned with a CUDA build here because
# the wheel must come from the CUDA index URL. See README + `make setup-gpu`.
# The default `make setup` installs the CPU torch wheel so the smoke test runs
# anywhere; `make setup-gpu` swaps in the H100 (cu124) wheels.
# =============================================================================

